				<td colspan="2"><span>Well this is one bard who has wished for dire charm on many occations.  The fact that they are level 46 pets (for chanters etc) means often we will not be able to find something to dire charm, but if we can, cool.  bard pets are very useful.  I miss the days when I could CC 6 mobs with easy, because i'd charm one, make it fight the second, and mez 3 through 6 (maybe even #7).  Now the things I normally fight are all out of charm range, so I can only CC 4 or 5, and that only if I have a head start on mezzing before they rip us all new ones, since they usually hit for 1K+.  Dire charm would do two things, it would allow me to do more dps (not that bard dps is half as crappy as people think, cause to be accurate you SHOULD figure in the dps boost you give the rest of the group too) but it would also allow me an extra moment during an &quot;oh crap&quot; pull, cause I could sacrifice my obedient pet to hold up a mob or two while i sang mez.</span></td>
