				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Dire charm<a name="52353"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 16 04 11:53 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>A dire charm pet, when hasted, is 80+ DPS. Add that to your own, and you are closing in or equal to the DPS of other hybrid classes. Yes, you can charm a 57 mob, but it only lasts 1 min max, and you probably don't want to haste it. Chances are, you don't even have that song memmed in most group situations. A DC pet, however, is very low maintenance and very low risk. The only times DC breaks is if you invis or the pet is dispelled (I guess FM would break it to). 
<br />

<br />
Anyway, bards getting DC will not happen, so I'm not too worried about arguing this. </span></td>
