				<td colspan="2"><span>Responding to keiz mainly now:
<br />

<br />
Did VI send you a copy of The Vision? Because I don't think bards were ever intended to be a super charming class. In fact, I feel that charm in all forms has become unbalanced. Charm back in original EQ was fine, because you couldn't charm a 500 DPS pet. Now you can. As a result, all charms for all classes are nerfed. Enchanters should be and are the primary charm class, with druids and necros falling into secondary roles. Enchanters can use charm as CC, but it's fairly rare. Necros and druids never use it for CC. It's usually used as DPS now. I feel this is not what charm was originally intended for. 
<br />

<br />
Before PoP was before PoP. Things will change. The Vision is dead now. Maybe bards were originally intended to charm, but then charm became overpowered and bards were powerful, so enchanters had to exceed bard charming abilities. Would you rather than enchanters had overhaste and bards had megacharm? I don't. 
<br />

<br />
A bard already fills many roles that overlap with enchanters. Like CC. A bard is more than adequate CC in normal LDoN, assuming you aren't pulling 15 mobs. Your group can get KEI before going in, and add bard manasong to that. Grab a group haste or let the bard manage it, and you are ready to roll, enchanter free. TBH, enchanters are more powerful for their charm than any other ability. Should bards suddenly take that too? The Vision has been replaced by a desire for balance, and bards are already powerful enough. 
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Not to mention WE CAN'T EVEN BUFF THE PET and they all can. </span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
But they actually have this thing called risk. Unlike bards, they can't FM out of a bad situation or just run around and recharm on the run. Ever charmed w/ a non bard? It's hardly easy. That 500 DPS pet is ready to rip you a new one if you aren't very careful and fairly lucky. </span></td>
